{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id12909440-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c","identifier":"/us/usc/t4/s122"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"122"},"text":"§ 122.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Determination of place of primary use","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id12909441-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c","identifier":"/us/usc/t4/s122/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Place of Primary Use","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"A home service provider shall be responsible for obtaining and maintaining the customer’s place of primary use (as defined in section 124). Subject to section 121, and if the home service provider’s reliance on information provided by its customer is in good faith, a taxing jurisdiction shall—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id12909442-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c","identifier":"/us/usc/t4/s122/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" allow a home service provider to rely on the applicable residential or business street address supplied by the home service provider’s customer; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id12909443-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c","identifier":"/us/usc/t4/s122/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" not hold a home service provider liable for any additional taxes, charges, or fees based on a different determination of the place of primary use for taxes, charges, or fees that are customarily passed on to the customer as a separate itemized charge.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id12909444-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c","identifier":"/us/usc/t4/s122/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Address Under Existing Agreements","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Except as provided in section 121, a taxing jurisdiction shall allow a home service provider to treat the address used by the home service provider for tax purposes for any customer under a service contract or agreement in effect 2 years after the date of the enactment of the Mobile Telecommunications Sourcing Act as that customer’s place of primary use for the remaining term of such service contract or agreement, excluding any extension or renewal of such service contract or agreement, for purposes of determining the taxing jurisdictions to which taxes, charges, or fees on charges for mobile telecommunications services are remitted.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id12909445-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/252/s2/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–252, § 2(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-07-28"},"text":"July 28, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/630"},"text":"114 Stat. 630","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id12909446-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id12909447-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id12909448-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The date of the enactment of the Mobile Telecommunications Sourcing Act, referred to in subsec. (b), is the date of enactment of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/252"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–252","children":[],"tail":", which was approved "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-07-28"},"text":"July 28, 2000","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id12909449-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"id1290944a-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date; Application of Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-07-28"},"text":"July 28, 2000","children":[],"tail":", and applicable only to customer bills issued after the first day of the first month beginning more than 2 years after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-07-28"},"text":"July 28, 2000","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/252/s3"},"text":"section 3 of Pub. L. 106–252","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t4/s116"},"text":"section 116 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
